03:31.880 --> 03:36.040
What is non-programmatic automation?

03:36.040 --> 03:41.800
This is the concept of you've automated something, but it doesn't necessarily have computer control.

03:41.800 --> 03:51.280
It's not something that you can programmatically adjust and basically control.

03:51.280 --> 03:55.320
Things like, I don't know how many of you are old enough to remember that years ago

03:55.320 --> 04:00.080
you used to have timers that you'd plug into lamps and you'd have a dial.

04:00.080 --> 04:01.080
Yeah, okay.

04:01.080 --> 04:02.640
Yeah, you still have them.

04:02.640 --> 04:03.640
That's good.

04:03.640 --> 04:05.240
Although, there's older people who are raising their hand.

04:05.240 --> 04:10.400
There's just one younger person there, but they'd have a dial and you'd turn it and you'd

04:10.400 --> 04:11.400
set the time.

04:11.400 --> 04:17.600
Then every time you lost power, you had to go back and set the dial to the right time.

04:17.600 --> 04:20.520
That is not programmatic automation.

04:20.520 --> 04:23.000
How many people have heard of something called the clapper?

04:23.000 --> 04:25.200
Oh my goodness.

04:25.200 --> 04:26.200
Yeah.

04:26.200 --> 04:31.160
If you want a howl, take a look at an old commercial video.

04:31.160 --> 04:35.520
It basically was a lamp that you would clap your hands and it would turn on and then you'd

04:35.520 --> 04:37.480
clap your hands and it would turn off.

