04:59.120 --> 05:00.120
the idea of motion sensors.

05:00.120 --> 05:04.440
Somebody would get close to the garage or walking to an entryway and the light would

05:04.440 --> 05:05.440
go on.

05:05.440 --> 05:06.440
Very convenient.

05:06.440 --> 05:08.720
Not programmatic, but very convenient.

05:08.720 --> 05:12.600
Then we're going to talk about programmatic automation.

05:12.600 --> 05:19.560
This has really exploded in the past, I don't know, five years I'd say.

05:19.560 --> 05:26.280
For example, the concept of voice automation, voice control is something that obviously

05:26.280 --> 05:29.280
really didn't exist effectively 20 years ago.

05:29.280 --> 05:32.640
Now it's hugely popular.

05:32.640 --> 05:40.240
The interesting thing about programmatic automation is that it allows you to take, you see the

05:40.240 --> 05:45.920
non-programmatic automation, the automation was kind of built into the device.

05:45.920 --> 05:52.320
You had the clapper or you had a motion sensor or you had a dawn dust sensor.

05:52.320 --> 05:54.160
You couldn't really change it.

05:54.160 --> 05:56.960
It was wired into how the device behaved.

05:56.960 --> 06:01.280
You couldn't combine that with some other device or combine it with some other inputs

06:01.280 --> 06:03.240
and make something different happen.

06:03.240 --> 06:07.600
Not that it wasn't useful, but programmatic allows you to combine behavior.

06:07.600 --> 06:10.440
It also allows you to do distance things.

06:10.440 --> 06:18.400
Again, one of the examples would be somebody comes into the garage, the garage door is

06:18.400 --> 06:25.080
open and some other action happens somewhere else in the house.

06:25.080 --> 06:29.440
Not usually something that would happen in a non-programmatic way, but it's easy to do

06:29.440 --> 06:32.960
if you're on a network of some type.

06:32.960 --> 06:40.360
Activity detection, being able to write scripts and basically programs that control with the

06:40.360 --> 06:43.280
automation incredibly powerful.

06:43.280 --> 06:47.920
Then finally, and I'll talk about this a little later, the idea of even bringing in external

06:47.920 --> 06:52.600
data and having the external data affect your home automation.

06:52.600 --> 06:56.800
For example, how cold is it outside?

06:56.800 --> 07:04.180
