13:11.800 --> 13:13.920
Choosing the network.

13:13.920 --> 13:17.240
Let's suppose you're going to use some network technology or you're going to use some kind

13:17.240 --> 13:18.240
of home automation.

13:18.240 --> 13:24.840
One of the first things you have to figure out is what do I want to measure and what

13:24.840 --> 13:27.040
do I want to control?

13:27.040 --> 13:33.240
Because effectively all of the home automation is really like an input output kind of a case.

13:33.240 --> 13:36.320
When this happens, this other thing's supposed to happen.

13:36.320 --> 13:42.520
Or when I see this activity, I want some other activity to happen.

13:42.520 --> 13:50.440
You have to identify if you're going to choose a particular technology, is it a multi protocol

13:50.440 --> 13:51.440
technology?

13:51.440 --> 13:55.840
Does it something like matter that can operate with multiple things or is it more like a

13:55.840 --> 14:01.720
Phillips hub that only really controls like Phillips devices?

